  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In this regard, blockchain's guarantees of data sovereignty, obfuscation, and traceability offer practical passive privacy benefits that align well with the requirements of LLMs.",
    "In particular, we observe blockchain-based privacy preservation techniques which originate in varying proximity to LLMs as seen in BC4LLMs itself [113,118,103], blockchain-enabled deep learning [147,55,121,120,96], blockchain-enabled machine learning [7], and blockchain-enabled federated learning [8,81,143,88,32,89,73].",
    "Within our focus on BC4LLMs, we have observed distinct trends in the application of blockchain to LLMs in their capacity to bolster passive privacy guarantees.",
    "Most notably, the development of zero-knowledge LLMs, a.k.a.",
    "ZK-LLMs, as described in [118] and [103], has the potential to drastically reduce privacy leakage risks when interacting with LLMs."
  ],
